    <p>Lifespan: 30-40 years</p>
    <p>Top speed: 12 mph</p>
    <p>Weight: 5-7 lbs, with females being slightly larger than males</p>
    <p>Diet: Invertebrates including beetles and insects, berries, seeds</p>
    <p>Predators: Birds of prey such as swamp harriers, introduced mammals such as cats, dogs, and ferrets</p>
    <p>Range: South island of New Zealand</p>
    <p>Conservation Status: Vulnerable</p>
    <div class="panel2">
        <p>Fun Fact: Kiwis lay one gg at a time, and the egg is 20% of the mother's body weight. It is the largest egg compared to body size of any bird.</p>
    </div>
    <br>
    <div class="panel4">
        <p>Fun Fact: Kiwis have nostrils at the end of their beak to smell for prey, as they have poor eyesight. They also have whiskers.</p>
